1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,640
If there's rain, they're singing songs or reading books together.

2
00:00:09,640 --> 00:00:16,280
Every day just has a way of feeling extra lucky.

3
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:21,760
When you spend it with a friend, just like Bjorn and Bucky.

4
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:24,960
Just like Bjorn and Bucky!

5
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:26,560
Global Warming

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:42,960
Wait, wait, don't go!

7
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:49,920
It's too darn hot!

8
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:55,120
Now I know what a potato feels like when it's baking.

9
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:58,240
What a heat wave we're going through.

10
00:00:58,240 --> 00:01:00,240
Phew, boy!

11
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,240
What a scorcher!

12
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:05,920
Wish I could take my fur off.

13
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,360
Hmm.

14
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:09,360
Genius time!

15
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:11,200
Must beat the heat!

16
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:12,560
Huh?

17
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:15,200
Poor little overheated beak face!

18
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,240
Chicky!

19
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:22,160
Don't worry!

20
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:23,760
I'll cool you down, pal!

21
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:25,680
Wait there!

22
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:26,960
Here!

23
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:27,360
And here!

24
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:28,720
Also here!

25
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:30,880
Also also here!

26
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:31,280
And here!

27
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,040
And here too!

28
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:36,800
Now, which wire leads to what?

29
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:40,160
Was it red or blue?

30
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:41,440
Or was it gray or gray?

31
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:43,360
I better unplug them both.

32
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:45,360
Just to be certain.

33
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:47,440
They're alive!

34
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,160
Alive!

35
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:51,840
You are so lucky to have a friend as smart as me.

36
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,440
You'll be cool in no time.

37
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:56,320
I just need to get some nice refreshing drinks from the fridge now.

38
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,800
Come to me, my lemonade!

39
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:00,000
Whoa!

40
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,640
No way!

41
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:04,160
It's even too hot inside the fridge!

42
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:08,480
This isn't just a heat wave.

43
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:11,840
This heat must be the work of global warming!

44
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,560
Well, all right then.

45
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:18,560
It's time to invent something that protects us from Mr. Sun!

46
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:22,240
This is my best idea ever!

47
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,840
Beat the heat!

48
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:28,960
Yeah!

49
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:41,520
Hi, Bucky!

50
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,440
I brought you some nice cold fruit punch!

51
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,360
Franny, thanks!

52
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:47,040
But I don't have time for punch!

53
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:49,280
I'm doing something really important!

54
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:53,440
Can you not see that I'm working hard on a machine that will block out the sun?

55
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,320
Great!

56
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,920
Why would you need to block out the sun?

57
00:02:56,800 --> 00:03:00,400
To save the world from the terrors of global warming!

58
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,120
Look, Franny!

59
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,120
Just need a few props!

60
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,920
And there!

61
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:08,880
Say you're relaxing in the sun, just catching some rays,

62
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,720
and you start to get a little extra hot.

63
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:15,520
You start up your sweet sunblockinator-o-matic-tron and...

64
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,080
Shade!

65
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,680
Even on the hottest of days!

66
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:22,320
Huh?

67
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:25,840
A fire?

68
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,520
Looks like it's near Bucky's place!

69
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:29,200
I'm coming to rescue you, buddy!

70
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:34,240
Oh, Bjorn!

71
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,200
Hi there!

72
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,240
Want some fruit punch?

73
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,040
Hey there!

74
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,160
Bucky?

75
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,720
So, what's burning?

76
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,880
Nothing's burning!

77
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:44,000
It's worse!

78
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,560
Global warming is ravaging our planet!

79
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:49,040
Bjorn, my poor fridge is no longer cold!

80
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,560
It got warmed!

81
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,920
This is bad!

82
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:54,080
Hurry, we've gotta save our forest!

83
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:57,440
So, will you two boys have some of my punch or not?

84
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,040
Who cares about the punch?

85
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,280
Don't you die on us, forest!

86
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,080
Hey, come on!

87
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:06,000
Pump it, guys!

88
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,080
Keep on pumping it!

89
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:08,800
That's great!

90
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:12,160
You picked the wrong globe to warm, buster!

91
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,760
Put your back into it!

92
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,200
So, hero-esque!

93
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,520
Well, guess I should put the punch in the fridge!

94
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,760
Who cares about the punch?

95
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:20,880
The stuff is delicious!

96
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:22,800
That's weird.

97
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:24,880
It's been turned off.

98
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:27,040
Odd choice on such a hot day.

99
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,080
Oh, the pluggy's outie!

100
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,000
There you go, sweetie!

101
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:35,040
Now it'll cool right down!

102
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,080
See you later, Punchy!

103
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:38,640
Pump, you pumpers!

104
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,160
Pump like the wind!

105
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:40,960
Yes!

106
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,880
Take that, global warming!

107
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:45,280
Fellas, I'm heading home.

108
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:48,800
Bucky, I plugged your fridge back in for you and left some punch.

109
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:49,440
K, bye!

110
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:52,240
Uh, huh?

111
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:55,120
It wasn't global warming that did it then?

112
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:58,960
All this time, I unplugged the refrigerator myself?

113
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:03,760
And we both thought that we were saving the entire forest!

114
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:07,280
Pump, guys!

115
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,560
Pump like the wind!

116
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:15,520
That's Franny the Fox one, global warming zero!

117
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,800
Want some fruit punch?

118
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,320
That sounds amazing!

119
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,240
It's really hot out today!

120
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:29,840
Well, that's global warming for ya!

